unittitle.value: Records of the Office of the Treasurer

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: This collection contains annual reports and financial reports created by the Office of the Treasurer.

p.value:
This collection is in
                <extref ns2:href="http://www.nyu.edu/library/bobst/research/arch/treasurer.htm">
                    <archref> off-site storage</archref> </extref>.

Published citations should take the following form:
                <lb/>
                <lb/>Identification of item, date (if known); The Records of the Office of the Treasurer; RG 10.2; box number; folder number;
                <lb/>
                <address>
                    <addressline>New York University Archives</addressline>
                </address>

The Office of the Treasurer, now called the Office of Finance, is responsible for financing transactions, the University's relation with banks, management of short-term cash, overseeing the Bursar's Ofice and Insurance Department, and processing gifts to the University.
This collection contains annual reports and financial reports created by the Office of the Treasurer.
